## Step 2 — Scaffold activities

### Activity struct pattern

```go
package activities

type <Resource><Operation>Activity struct {
	SE database.Storage
}
```

### Activity method pattern

```go
func (a *<Resource><Operation>Activity) <ActionName>(ctx context.Context, args ...) (ResultType, error) {
	activity.RecordHeartbeat(ctx, "Starting <ActionName>")
	logger := util.GetLogger(ctx)

	// Business logic here
	result, err := someOperation(ctx, args...)
	if err != nil {
		logger.Errorf("<ActionName> failed: %v", err)
		return nil, vsaerrors.WrapAsTemporalApplicationError(
			fmt.Errorf("failed to <action>: %w", err),
		)
	}

	activity.RecordHeartbeat(ctx, "Completed <ActionName>")
	return result, nil
}
```

### Error wrapping rules for activities

| Scenario | Wrapper |
|----------|---------|
| Transient failure (network, timeout) | `vsaerrors.WrapAsTemporalApplicationError(err)` |
| Permanent failure (validation, not-found) | `vsaerrors.WrapAsNonRetryableTemporalApplicationError(err)` |
| Known error code | `vsaerrors.NewVCPError(vsaerrors.ErrXxx, err)` then wrap |
| Custom error with args | `vsaerrors.NewVCPErrorWithArgs(code, err, arg1, arg2)` |

